\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 LogiBraiding guides braid execution step by step and keeps the screen intentionally simple.
\par The top bar contains the braid selector, the Sequential button, the interval selector, the countdown, the AuthorID / Trial status, Drawing, Doc, Menu, and the details button.
\par The instruction panel displays the current action. The visible buttons are the check mark for the next move and the cross for restart.
\par 
\par Tip
\par The instruction panel text should be sufficient on its own, while the braiding table confirms the action visually.
\par 
\par Sequential mode
\par Sequential mode automatically reproduces a click on the next-move button after the selected delay. It does not slow down the line drawing; it only controls the rhythm of the displayed steps.
\par Available intervals are 5 s, 10 s, 15 s, 20 s, 30 s, 40 s, 50 s, and 60 s.
\par The countdown displays the seconds remaining before the next step.
\par At the end of a cycle, the last move is executed, step 1 of the next sequence is displayed, and Sequential mode stops automatically.
\par 
\par Warning
\par Sequential mode is not a graphical demo mode. It simply gives the braider enough time to perform the real move before the next step appears.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb40\sl259\slmult1\keep\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6192288 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503\afs26\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
