\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Ribbon: the knot is built on a millimeter grid ribbon with adjustable length (430 mm by default in many current projects).
\par Ropes: up to five ropes can be used. The active rope receives new points. Rope selection is done with Ctrl+1 to Ctrl+5.
\par Crossings: Crossings mode, activated with Ctrl+C, is used to correct over/under direction. Inversions are saved and restored when the file is reloaded.
\par Validation: a validated .lkv file becomes non-editable. To resume from an editable version, first use Copy.
\par 
\par Warning
\par Validation is not just a save. It represents a final state intended for consultation, archiving, or stable printing.
