\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Sketch mode is used to build or transform temporary geometry before returning to actual tracing.
\par The first click places an anchor.
\par Subsequent clicks add sketch segments from this anchor.
\par Space interrupts the current sketch.
\par Shift + mouse drag creates a selection.
\par Shift + mouse drag on an existing selection moves it.
\par Ctrl + Shift + mouse drag duplicates the selection and moves it.
\par 
\par The commands Rotate right 90 degrees, Rotate left 90 degrees, Flip vertically, and Flip horizontally apply to the active selection.
\par 
\par Warning
\par Sketch mode does not replace the final traced rope. It is used to prepare, correct, or move segments before integrating them into the knot logic. Crossings are not defined in sketch mode.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb40\sl259\slmult1\keep\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6192288 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503\afs26\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
