\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Crossings mode is used to correct over/under direction and to copy the crossing order from one segment to another. Crossin
gs modified during the session are marked visually. Inversions are saved and restored when the file is reloaded.
\par Esc leaves this mode. Right-click on a hovered crossing inverts it.
\par In this mode, left-click on a segment selects it as the source segment. Then left-click on another compatible segment copies the crossing order onto that segment. If the selected source segment is clicked again, the selection is cancelled.
\par When the mouse hovers a crossing, the tooltip shows Left Crossing or Right Crossing and reminds the user that right-click inverts it.
\par 
\par Tip
\par Correcting a crossing as soon as a doubt appears avoids inconsistencies later, during preparation or at print time.
\par 
