\par File and printing
\par Ctrl+O: open an .lkw or .lkv file
\par Ctrl+S: save the working file
\par Ctrl+P: print
\par File menu > Validate: lock as .lkv
\par File menu > Copy: create an editable copy
\par 
\par View and navigation
\par Ctrl++: zoom in
\par Ctrl+-: zoom out
\par Ctrl+0: zoom 100%
\par Home: return the junction to the ribbon origin
\par 
\par Modes
\par Ctrl+E: Sketch mode
\par Ctrl+B: Tracing mode
\par Ctrl+C: enter or leave Crossings mode
\par Esc: leave Crossings mode
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Ribbon rotation
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Left or Right arrow: 1 mm step
\par Shift + Left or Right arrow: 5 mm step
\par Ctrl + Left or Right arrow: 10 mm step
\par Alt + Left or Right arrow: shorten or lengthen the ribbon by 1 mm
\par Alt + Ctrl + Left or Right arrow: 5 mm step
\par Alt + Ctrl + Shift + Left or Right arrow: 10 mm step
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Ropes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Ctrl+1 to Ctrl+5: choose the active rope
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Sketch mode
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Ctrl+E activates Sketch mode.
\par The first left click places an anchor (green sketch point).
\par Subsequent clicks add sketch segments from that anchor.
\par Space interrupts the current sketch to start elsewhere.
\par Selection: hold Shift and drag a rectangle around the sketch you want to select.
\par Keep Shift pressed during the operation.
\par Delete or Backspace removes the active selection.
\par Ctrl+Shift+C copies the selection.
\par Ctrl+V pastes the selection at the current position.
\par Ctrl+Z and Ctrl+Y then act on the sketch, not on the traced rope.
\par In Sketch mode you can move a sketch:
\par grab the selection and move it by dragging the mouse.
\par Releasing Shift in Sketch mode ends the move and clears the selection.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Crossings management
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 During design, the rope systematically passes over the crossed rope.
\par Crossings must therefore be corrected once tracing is complete.
\par Press Ctrl+C to enter Crossings mode.
\par Crossings then appear surrounded by a circle.
\par In Crossings mode, right-click on a hovered crossing inverts it. It is then marked in translucent red. This marking is not permanent and di
sappears after reloading a future session; it only indicates that this crossing was modified during the current session.
\par When hovering a segment, left-click selects the source segment and copies its crossing order. You can then hover another compatible segment and left-click again to copy the same crossing order in the same sequence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Notes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31506 \ltrch\fcs0 \f31506\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7733306\charrsid12002340 Undo (Ctrl+Z) and Redo (Ctrl+Y) only affect commands from the current mode. Actions in Tracing mode and Sketch mode are handled separately.
\par In a validated .lkv file, editing commands are disabled.
\par 
\par 
